##Wuhan Doctor Post Station: 40,000 people are provided with accommodation, some quit and some stay

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

According to statistics from the support alliance, starting from January 23,271 hotels in the Wuhan area (about 47 in other cities in Hubei) provided free accommodation for medical staff until 9 p.m. on January 30, in total, the alliance provided more than 40,000 overnight accommodations for 6,056 health care workers.

City Convenient Hotel Children's palace shop provides free snacks for medical staff. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

By Xiang Kai, Beijing News

Editor | Jay Hu

This article is about 4,184 words long and takes about 8 minutes to read

On January 31, the Wuhan Medical and Nursing Hotel Support Union (hereinafter referred to as the Support Union) announced that 159 single-hotel, bed and breakfast, apartment and small chain hotels in the Wuhan area will no longer receive medical and nursing staff. About a week into operation, the voluntary group supporting the fight against the new type of pneumonia in the Wuhan Hotel Industry ceased some of its services.

Xiao Yaxing, 27, the main sponsor of the support alliance, told the Beijing News that the reason for the suspension of the reception was that individual and small hotels could not bear the long-term risks and costs due to the uncertain situation, "Overall attrition and operating costs are the two biggest issues. "

At 10:00 am on January 23, Wuhan officially closed the Lihan Corridor, and the city's subway, bus, ferry and long-distance passenger transport were suspended. In order to solve the problem of accommodation for medical staff, there are many hotels in Wuhan which provide accommodation for medical staff voluntarily and free of charge. According to statistics from the support alliance, starting from January 23,271 hotels in the Wuhan area (about 47 in other cities in Hubei) provided free accommodation for medical staff until 9 p.m. on January 30, in total, the alliance provided more than 40,000 overnight accommodations for 6,056 health care workers.

The Hsinking news reporter has learned that the hotels supporting the alliance to stop receiving medical staff do not include major hotel chains such as Dongcheng and Botao. With the arrival of medical rescue teams from other provinces and cities, the demand for hotels by medical staff continues to increase, the government, the hospital commandeers the whole or uses the hotel to provide the accommodation for the medical personnel the movement is still in progress.

Launched on New Year's Eve, snowballing growth

Xiao Yaxing, 27, is the founder of the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance. The post-90s girl has the directness typical of Wuhan people and speaks quickly. Xiao Yaxing told the Beijing News that he first saw many pictures of doctors and nurses sleeping in their offices and beds after working overtime on the Internet and felt that something should be done. Because he is a hotel practitioners, they began to organize around the hotel industry friends, called for medical staff to provide accommodation.

"[ on New Year's Eve ] at 5:43 pm I set up the 'Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Group' . By 12 pm there were 86, by 10:00 am the next day there were 100, and on the third day, large hotel chains joined, and soon there were more than 300. "

Soon after the construction of the cluster, Xiao Yaxing announced in the cluster that "Wuhan is recruiting free accommodation for medical and nursing staff" to solicit housing resources, "As long as there are vacant rooms, residents in the community should not complain and provide a clean and independent living environment, " she said. She also issued "notes for people and businesses staying in private hotels. " Remind health care workers to bring their own four-piece sets, Disposable and disinfectant, etc. ; hotel staff to do a good job of protection, check out with 75% medical alcohol disinfection... "after all, is the reception of health care workers, safety is the first. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 30, Yuet Oriental Hotel volunteers to prepare supplies. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

On the Internet, the list of hotels available for medical staff is open, with detailed hotel addresses, telephone numbers, number of available rooms, nearby hospitals and so on. The list spread quickly on New Year's Eve, with hotels ranging from 10 to 86, to more than 100, and finally to 318, covering more than 10 districts in Wuhan. Medical personnel only need to check in with ID card, work card, for convenience, the hotel will open a one-to-two-week room card.

A small hotel chain staff told the Beijing News that she joined after seeing Xiao Yaxing's recruitment news and posted the hotel's address and contact information online. "from the evening of New Year's Eve to 7 am the next day, five nurses from Wuhan Central Hospital checked into one of her hotels on New Year's Eve.

Xiao Yaxing said that since the phone number on the Internet, a day to receive hundreds of inquiries about housing calls is common, the first full is near the hospital hotel. So far, every day there are gold and Silver Pool, concord and other hospital medical staff to call the hotel information.

Jiang Heng is the director of the Youth Palace of the city convenient hotel chain. He told the reporter that the city convenient hotel chain started to provide accommodation for medical staff on January 25.

"At first, it was single hotels, bed-and-breakfast, apartments, and even some of their vacant rental rooms were put up for the medical staff to live in. It spread like a snowball through the circles of friends and the industry, " Jiang said.

The voluntary forces of the people have levered up greater resources. January 25, Dongcheng, Botao and other large-scale hotel chains also provide free accommodation for medical staff, the number of doctor stations increased.

"after the suspension of public transport, I immediately reported to the Chairman of the board of directors. The board of directors had an emergency meeting and immediately arranged to have 10,000 guest rooms available in Hubei. It took us 10 hours to get 10,000 guest rooms ready, " Dong Cheng group Hubei President, Lai Shiming, told the Beijing News, so far has been connected to dozens of hospitals in Wuhan, medical staff admitted nearly 20,000 person-times.

January 29, the city's Convenient Hotel Youth Palace for medical staff check-in. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

The doctor's post was almost full every day

At 6.20 pm on January 30, Huang Wanying (not her real name) , lugging a suitcase and a packed lunch, entered the Yue Dong Hotel, a small hotel near the Wuchang Railway Station, it began to become a "doctor's station" offering free accommodation for medical staff.

Huang Wanying, a nurse at the Hubei Provincial People's Hospital, walked into the room with the lobby lights off and no one at the front desk.

Huang Wanying told the Beijing News that her home in Hanyang is fifty 10 minutes by subway, while her hotel is less than 2 kilometers from the hospital and a 20 minute walk away.

In some of the hotels that provide free accommodation for the staff, family members bring daily necessities, washbasins, clothes and snacks to the staff, and some staff bring electric blankets. Due to the Spring Festival holiday, hotel cleaning and linen washing companies are not working, medical staff to bring their own bedding and daily necessities.

"considering family members, we can not take the risk of infection home with us, " a medical worker surnamed Wang told the Beijing News. "self-isolation can also be achieved in a hotel. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the afternoon of January 30, a paramedic checked into the Yuet Tung Hotel. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

At the beginning of the operation of the support alliance, most of the medical staff to see the hotel staff, volunteers in the online information, directly with the hotel. Jiang Heng, director of the Youth Palace of the city's convenient hotel chain, said that at first he also posted the phone number and hotel address on the Internet, but later found that such one-to-one communication with medical staff delayed time, and he was directly connected with the hospital, "Let the hospital coordinate staff, collective occupancy, saving communication costs. " His hotel has 108 rooms, almost full every day, mainly in Wuhan No. 6 Hospital and Union Hospital Staff.

There are also hospitals that concentrate on arranging hotels for their staff in the immediate vicinity. A medical staff member of the Third Hospital in Wuhan told the Beijing News that employees who live far away and are unable to return home can apply to the department, which will report to the hospital's trade union, which will contact the hotel. According to his introduction, the designated hotel of the three hospitals is only one kilometer away from the hospital.

Security is a top priority at the doctor's station.

Wu Jie, a worker at the city's convenient youth palace store, has rarely seen medical staff since she took up her post. She has set up a wechat group. The medical staff who check in are all in the group. On weekdays, they basically do not speak, in addition to someone asked how to turn on the television, the remote control to replace the battery, etc. . "They were in the hospital every day with patients, and they were very careful themselves, and when they came back they hurried into their rooms and did not linger in the public areas. "

"The staff would also tell us not to go into their rooms and not to touch anything they had touched, " said a hotel official, who said they would clean up after themselves when they moved out.

Some hotels do not have the front desk staff, the medical staff registration, the room card on the front desk, medical staff, other things are online communication.

"In times of emergency, it is very touching to be able to help us travel, to have a place to live, and to feel that Wuhan is a warm city, " said a medical worker at Wuhan's Third Hospital,

Visible problems and invisible risks

Ming told the reporter that the doctor station faced three major problems: in addition to security risks, but also faced with hotel staff, protective materials shortage and operating costs.

The company called on its remaining employees in Wuhan to return to work because of the Lunar New Year holiday. "some employees work up to 12-15 hours a day, " the company said

The lack of supplies is more worrying than the lack of manpower. Although the medical staff are in a high-risk industry, they have professional protection and knowledge. The front-line staff of the hotel only have a mask and a bottle of 84 disinfectant, "Every day there are suspected infections, and then ruled out, the total fear of wolves really one day. "

At the Yuet Oriental Hotel on January 30, a reporter saw staff carrying supplies wearing a thin layer of disposable plastic gloves due to a lack of medical disposable gloves.

Jiang Heng introduced that the city convenient youth palace shop is arranged by the hospital for professional killing, twice a day. But in a small hotel like Yuet Tung, hospitals can't offer professional killing.

"Most of the individual hotels can not be used by the hospitals, and can not contact the hospital leaders and logistics, " Xiao Yaxing told the Beijing News. Even if the medical staff staying in the hotels could send word to the hospitals or ask for contact information from the hospital leaders, no one has been able to provide.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 30, Yuet Oriental Hotel on the first floor of the lobby of the disinfection water. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

Even for large hotel chains, cost is a big problem. The next Ming, the current docking dozens of hotels, except for a few government requisition of the intention to propose subsidies, most of the current without any subsidies.

Xiao Yaxing's Yue Dong Fang hotel is a small hotel with about 50 rooms, mainly spent on electricity, at least 1,200 yuan a day.

Jiang Heng's city Youth Palace Hotel, including rent, water and electricity costs about 400,000 a month.

But for the single hotel, in addition to the visible problem, but also face the invisible risk and doubt.

On January 27, volunteers from Xiao Yaxing's team drove to a company in Xiantaola to donate face masks, protective clothing and other materials. Due to the road ban, they needed a pass to enter and exit Wuhan, they had a hard time getting a pass from the Wuchang District Health Bureau to get out of Wuhan, but they had to get a pass to get back from Xiantao to Wuhan. "supply vehicles came in asking for special letters from hospitals, but many refused to open them. "

Few hospitals offer to receive letters of acceptance, Xiao said. "We want a letter from the hospital offering free accommodation for their staff, and many hospitals are reluctant to do so. "

Xiao Yaxing said that since the support league called for accommodation for medical staff, gloves, masks, protective clothing, etc. , all need to solve themselves. When the hotel was short of protective materials, she organized volunteers to call one factory after another to ask for help. She collected transportation vehicles to bring back the sterilized water.

In addition, the hotel is also faced with outside gossip, "For example, if someone says we have infected medical staff in our shop, we will not be able to do business from now on. There are many hotel staff heard that the boss received medical staff, are not back to work."Xiao Yaxing said.

We're GONNA switch over, and we're GONNA resupply the community with protective gear

On January 31, the Support League announced that 159 single, bed and breakfast, apartment and small chain hotels would no longer receive health care workers and guests, and that rooms would be cleared and ready to be disinfected by 1800 hours on January 31.

According to the support alliance announcement, the main suspension of services were individual hotels, bed-and-breakfast, etc. . The remaining 62 hotels and Major Hotel Chains, including Tung Shing, continued to provide accommodation for medical staff.

According to Ming's observation, now the government departments are mapping the regional hotel situation, there is a trend of co-ordination. "There is a command center in each district to map out the hotels in the district and coordinate with the hotel if they meet the requirements. "

Travel conditions for medical staff are also improving, with free buses and Didi taxis being organised in Wuhan to cater to medical staff. On January 29, a medical worker from the Lake Park Behind Wuhan's Central Hospital told the Beijing News that the bus had started running to pick up and drop off medical workers. The intensity of the work of the medical staff has slowed somewhat since the arrival of the medical rescue teams from all over the country.

As they prepare to pull out, she and her volunteers are working on another project -- as if she and her volunteers were buying total annihilation for the 159 small hotels in the support coalition, using funds they had previously raised, and the social resources that she amasses as a civic organizer, the materials that she raises, will be provided to the communities that are most in need. "The best thing to do now is to finish what you started. "

Under the Wuhan Municipal Government, the community took on the task of screening, isolating and transporting fever patients, becoming the first line of defense against exposure to fever patients.

"material donations start at the grass-roots level, first meet the needs of the grass-roots communities and then go to the organs, " Xiao Yaxing said. In recent days, they have donated materials to government departments, hospitals, community service centers and hotels. For every batch of materials donated, have to take photos, registration, let the other side to provide proof of receipt and seal, "because there have been false claim of the situation. "

Masks and protective clothing donated to the community on January 30. Photo by Xiang Kai, Hsinking Daily News

In a small courtyard near the Wuchang Railway Station, Xiao Yaxing operates a hotel that, because of its remoteness and lack of medical staff, redistributes supplies he has brought back from the field. A volunteer who works in Washing Hotel Linen brought back two one-ton containers of water to be mixed with disinfectant.

Xiao Yaxing told reporters that while 159 individual hotels, bed-and-breakfast, apartment and small hotel chains will no longer receive medical staff, the remaining 112 chains will continue to provide accommodation for medical staff. According to the assessment, even if some individual hotels, small chain hotels and other reception work, should also be able to meet the current demand.

"We are also looking at how to broaden the channels for these hotels. "
